   832	Capture loan requests from borrowers through offline, assisted or digital channels and ensure complete application intake.
   833	
   834	### Functional Requirements
   835	
   836	| Req ID | Requirement |
   837	|---|---|
   838	| M03-FR-001 | System shall allow application initiation by borrower, field officer, Credit Manager or Deputy Manager – Finance. |
   839	| M03-FR-002 | System shall capture application channel as offline, digital portal or assisted entry. |
   840	| M03-FR-003 | System shall capture folio number, share count, requested loan amount, purpose and nominee details. |
   841	| M03-FR-004 | System shall show system-calculated maximum permissible loan limit after required data is available. |
   842	| M03-FR-005 | System shall require applicant and nominee signatures, either digital or scanned physical copy. |
   843	| M03-FR-006 | System shall require borrower and nominee KYC uploads. |
   844	| M03-FR-007 | System shall require share certificate, 7/12 extract, crop plan and six-month bank statement. |
   845	| M03-FR-008 | System shall allow save-as-draft before submission. |
   846	| M03-FR-009 | System shall validate mandatory fields before submission. |
   847	| M03-FR-010 | System shall route submitted application to Deputy Manager – Finance for completeness check. |
   848	| M03-FR-011 | System shall generate deficiency list for incomplete applications. |
   849	| M03-FR-012 | System shall generate unique application number only after completeness passes. |
   850	
   851	### Application Reference Number
   852	
   853	The system must support the sequence:
   854	
   855	```text
   856	LO00000001
   857	LO00000002
   858	LO00000003
   859	...
   860	```
   861	
   862	The sequence must be unique, non-repeating and auditable. Cancelled or rejected applications should not result in reused numbers.
   863	
   864	### Deficiency Flow
   865	
   866	1. Deputy Manager – Finance reviews submitted application.
   867	2. Missing fields / documents are marked.
   868	3. System generates deficiency note or Rejection Note as applicable.
   869	4. Borrower is notified through configured channel.
   870	5. Application enters `INCOMPLETE` state.
   871	6. Borrower / field officer resubmits.
   872	7. System keeps deficiency history.

